# React & Next.js Component Rules

Use when building or editing `.tsx` components for the Party Barn Mercantile site.

## App Router

- **Pages:** Use `app/[route]/page.tsx`. One default export; use async when fetching on the server.
- **Layouts:** Use `app/layout.tsx` for root (fonts, nav, footer); `app/(marketing)/layout.tsx` or route-specific layouts only when shared structure is needed. Keep layout trees shallow.
- **Server vs client:** Prefer server components. Add `"use client"` only for interactivity (forms, cart, modals, client-side Shopify cart mutations). Fetch Shopify data in server components or server actions when possible.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – server component, data at page level
export default async function ShopPage() {
  const collections = await getCollections();
  return <CollectionGrid collections={collections} />;
}

// ✅ GOOD – client only where needed
"use client";
export function AddToCartButton({ variantId }: { variantId: string }) {
  // cart mutation, etc.
}
```

## Components

- **Functional components only.** No class components.
- **Type props explicitly.** Prefer interfaces for component props; use Shopify types (e.g. from `@shopify/storefront-api-client` or project types) for product/collection data.
- **Extract reusable UI** (buttons, cards, section wrappers) into components; use Tailwind with brand classes (see party-barn-build rule for palette/fonts).
- **Headings:** Sauvage Serif for titles (e.g. `font-serif` if serif = Sauvage). JetBrains Mono for body and product copy (e.g. `font-mono`).

## Tailwind

- Use semantic brand colors from config (e.g. `bg-brand-cream`, `text-brand-ink`) rather than raw hex in JSX.
- Prefer Tailwind for layout and typography; avoid inline styles unless dynamic (e.g. CSS variable for a one-off).
- Keep responsive breakpoints consistent (e.g. `md:` for tablet, `lg:` for desktop).

## Data & Shopify

- **Server:** Call Storefront API (GraphQL) from server components or route handlers. Centralize client in `lib/shopify` or similar; use environment variables for store domain and token.
- **Product/collection lists:** Fetch in page or layout; pass as props. Avoid client-side fetching for initial product/collection data when SSR is possible.
- **Cart:** Cart state and mutations live in client components or context; create cart via Storefront API when needed (e.g. first add-to-cart).

## Accessibility & UX

- Use semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<button>` vs `<div>` for clickable UI.
- Form inputs: associate `<label>` with `<input>` (by `id`/`htmlFor`); indicate required and errors.
- Links: use Next.js `<Link>` for in-app navigation; external links can use `<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">` where appropriate.

## Don’t

- Use Pages Router for new routes; use App Router only.
- Fetch Shopify data in client components when the same data can be fetched on the server.
- Hardcode brand colors or fonts in components; use Tailwind theme/classes defined in the project config.
